<grammar><section><title>Adverbs</title><sectiontitle>We usually make an adverb by adding &lt;I&gt;-ly&lt;/I&gt; to the adjective.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_8_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>Interesting</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_8_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>Interesting&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;ly&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>Quick</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_8_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>Quick&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;ly&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><sectiontitle2>Some adverbs are irregular.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_8_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><text3>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;good&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; (adjective) &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;well&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; (adverb)</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_8_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>Do you feel &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;well&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;?</text3a><text4>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;hard&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; (adjective) &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;hard&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; (adverb)</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_8_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>Natasha works &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;hard&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text4a></section><section><title>Adverbs</title><sectiontitle>There are different types of adverbs: &lt;BR&gt;1) &lt;B&gt;Adverbs of manner;&lt;/B&gt; These adverbs describe how something happens - they modify the verb. Adverbs of manner usually come after the verb.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_8_2_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>%undefined</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_8_2_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>The news spread &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;quickly&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; around the office.</text1a><text2>%undefined</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_8_2_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>He held the baby &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;gently&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text2a><sectiontitle2>2) &lt;B&gt;Adverbs of frequency/probability;&lt;/B&gt; These adverbs describe how often something happens or how probable it is. They usually come before the main verb.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_8_2_10.mp3</titlesound2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_8_2_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>Newspapers &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;rarely&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; report on these important issues.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_8_2_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;nearly&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; caught the last train.</text4a></section><section><title>Adverbs</title><sectiontitle>3) &lt;B&gt;Adverbs of degree;&lt;/B&gt; These adverbs modify an adjective or a verb. They make it weaker or stronger.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_8_2_13.mp3</titlesound><text1>%undefined</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_8_2_14.mp3</sound1><text1a>It was &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;totally&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; unexpected.</text1a><text2>%undefined</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_8_2_15.mp3</sound2><text2a>He's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;quite&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; late.</text2a><sectiontitle2>4) &lt;B&gt;Adverbs which describe attitude;&lt;/B&gt; These adverbs describe the speaker's attitude towards the information in the clause.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_8_2_16.mp3</titlesound2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_8_2_17.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Luckily&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;, the money was still there when I returned.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_8_2_18.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Sadly&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;, we missed the end of the film.</text4a></section><section><title>Adverbs vs Adjectives</title><sectiontitle>Be careful! Some adjectives look like adverbs because they end in&lt;I&gt; -ly&lt;/I&gt; but they are not.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_8_2_19.mp3</titlesound><text1>silly   lovely   lively</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_8_2_20.mp3</sound1><text1a>Our cat is very &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;silly&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text1a><text2>%undefined</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_8_2_21.mp3</sound2><text2a>It's a &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;lively&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; city.</text2a><sectiontitle2>%undefined</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>%undefined</sound3><text3a>%undefined</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>%undefined</sound4><text4a>%undefined</text4a></section></grammar>